### Code:

```java
import javax.imageio.ImageIO;
import java.awt.image.BufferedImage;
import java.io.*;
import java.net.URL;

public class ImageFilterDownloader {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String imageUrl = "https://example.com/sample-image.jpg"; // Replace with your image URL
        String outputPath = "filtered-image.jpg";

        try {
            BufferedImage image = loadImageFromUrl(imageUrl);
            if (image == null) {
                System.out.println("Failed to load image from URL.");
                return;
            }

            BufferedImage filteredImage = applyFilter(image);
            saveImageToFile(filteredImage, outputPath);

            System.out.println("Image downloaded and filtered successfully.");
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    private static BufferedImage loadImageFromUrl(String url) throws IOException {
        URL imageUrl = new URL(url);
        BufferedImage image = ImageIO.read(imageUrl);
        if (image == null) {
            System.out.println("Failed to read image from URL.");
            return null;
        }
        return image;
    }

    private static BufferedImage applyFilter(BufferedImage image) {
        // Apply grayscale filter
        BufferedImage filtered = new BufferedImage(image.getWidth(), image.getHeight(), BufferedImage.TYPE_INT_RGB);
        for (int x = 0; x < image.getWidth(); x++) {
            for (int y = 0; y < image.getHeight(); y++) {
                int pixel = image.getRGB(x, y);
                int r = (pixel >> 16) & 0xFF;
                int g = (pixel >> 8) & 0xFF;
                int b = (pixel >> 0) & 0xFF;
                int gray = (r + g + b) / 3;
                filtered.setRGB(x, y, (gray << 16) | (gray << 8) | gray);
            }
        }
        return filtered;
    }

    private static void saveImageToFile(BufferedImage image, String outputPath) throws IOException {
        ImageIO.write(image, "jpg", new File(outputPath));
        System.out.println("Image saved to: " + outputPath);
    }
}
```

### How to Use:
1. Replace the `imageUrl` with the URL of the image you want to download.
2. Run the program.
3. The filtered image will be saved as `filtered-image.jpg` in the current directory.

### Notes:
- This example uses the `javax.imageio` library for image I/O.
- The grayscale filter is applied by converting each pixel to its grayscale equivalent.
- You can extend this program to apply other filters (e.g., blur, contrast, etc.) by modifying the `applyFilter` method.

